**3. Finding $t^2$**

The length of the tangent is the distance from the origin to the line $y = -\frac{q - p}{2 \sqrt{2pr - p^2}} x.$  Using the formula for the distance from a point to a line, we get
\[t = \frac{\left| -\frac{q - p}{2 \sqrt{2pr - p^2}} \cdot 0 - 0 \right|}{\sqrt{\left( -\frac{q - p}{2 \sqrt{2pr - p^2}} \right)^2 + 1^2}} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{\left( \frac{q - p}{2 \sqrt{2pr - p^2}} \right)^2 + 1}}.\]Squaring both sides, we get
